What the true proverb says has happened to them: “The dog returns to its own vomit, and the sow after washing herself returns to wallow in mire.”
For them the gloom of utter darkness has been reserved. They are blots and blemishes reveling in their deceptions while they feast with you. They have eyes full of adultery insatiable for sin. They entice unsteady souls. They have hearts trained in greed. Accursed children!
Forsaking the right way they have gone astray. They followed way of Balaam son of Beor who loved gain of wrongdoing but was rebuked for his own transgression. A speechless donkey spoke with human voice and restrained prophet’s madness.
They count it pleasure to revel in daytime. They are blots and blemishes reveling in their deceptions while they feast with you. They have eyes full of adultery insatiable for sin. They entice unsteady souls. They have hearts trained in greed. Accursed children!
These are waterless springs and mists driven by storm. For them gloom of utter darkness has been reserved.
They promise freedom but they themselves are slaves of corruption. For whatever overcomes person to that he is enslaved.
For if after escaping defilements of world through knowledge of our Lord and Savior Yeshua the Anointed they are again entangled in them and overcome the last state has become worse for them than first. For it would have been better for them never to have known way of righteousness than after knowing it to turn back from holy commandment delivered to them.
They have gone astray. They have followed way of Balaam who loved gain of wrongdoing.
